{
    "name": "GDPR Integrity Council (MAKGED v2)",
    "nodes": [
        {
            "parameters": {
                "httpMethod": "POST",
                "path": "validate-triple",
                "responseMode": "responseNode"
            },
            "id": "webhook-trigger",
            "name": "1. Webhook: Validate Triple",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
            "typeVersion": 2,
            "position": [
                250,
                400
            ],
            "webhookId": "validate-triple-webhook",
            "notes": "ENTRY: POST { triple: {head, relation, tail}, sourceText, requestId }"
        },
        {
            "parameters": {
                "jsCode": "const input = $input.first().json.body;\n\nconst triple = {\n  head: input.triple?.subject || input.triple?.head || 'Unknown',\n  relation: input.triple?.predicate || input.triple?.relation || 'UNKNOWN',\n  tail: input.triple?.object || input.triple?.tail || 'Unknown'\n};\n\nreturn {\n  json: {\n    triple: triple,\n    sourceText: input.sourceText || '',\n    requestId: input.requestId || null,\n    discussionRound: 1,\n    maxRounds: 3,\n    agentResponses: {},\n    started: new Date().toISOString()\n  }\n};"
            },
            "id": "prepare-input",
            "name": "2. Prepare Input",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
            "typeVersion": 2,
            "position": [
                470,
                400
            ]
        },
        {
            "parameters": {
                "promptType": "define",
                "text": "=## HEAD FORWARD AGENT - Round {{ $json.discussionRound }}\n\n**Triple:** ({{ $json.triple.head }}) --[{{ $json.triple.relation }}]--> ({{ $json.triple.tail }})\n**Source:** {{ $json.sourceText || 'No source provided' }}\n\nYou analyze OUTGOING relations FROM the head entity.\n\n1. First, use the Graph Query tool to check: What other relations does {{ $json.triple.head }} have as a source?\n2. Analyze if the proposed relation fits the pattern.\n3. If this is round 2+, consider previous agent arguments: {{ JSON.stringify($json.agentResponses) }}\n\nRespond JSON: { \"verdict\": \"CORRECT/INCORRECT\", \"confidence\": 0-10, \"evidence\": [], \"reasoning\": \"...\" }"
            },
            "id": "agent-head-forward",
            "name": "3a. Head Forward Agent",
            "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
            "typeVersion": 1.7,
            "position": [
                690,
                150
            ]
        },
        {
            "parameters": {
                "promptType": "define",
                "text": "=## HEAD BACKWARD AGENT - Round {{ $json.discussionRound }}\n\n**Triple:** ({{ $json.triple.head }}) --[{{ $json.triple.relation }}]--> ({{ $json.triple.tail }})\n**Source:** {{ $json.sourceText || 'No source provided' }}\n\nYou analyze INCOMING relations TO the head entity.\n\n1. Use the Graph Query tool: What points TO {{ $json.triple.head }}?\n2. Does the head entity's context support this new outgoing relation?\n3. Round 2+ considerations: {{ JSON.stringify($json.agentResponses) }}\n\nRespond JSON: { \"verdict\": \"CORRECT/INCORRECT\", \"confidence\": 0-10, \"evidence\": [], \"reasoning\": \"...\" }"
            },
            "id": "agent-head-backward",
            "name": "3b. Head Backward Agent",
            "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
            "typeVersion": 1.7,
            "position": [
                690,
                350
            ]
        },
        {
            "parameters": {
                "promptType": "define",
                "text": "=## TAIL FORWARD AGENT - Round {{ $json.discussionRound }}\n\n**Triple:** ({{ $json.triple.head }}) --[{{ $json.triple.relation }}]--> ({{ $json.triple.tail }})\n**Source:** {{ $json.sourceText || 'No source provided' }}\n\nYou analyze OUTGOING relations FROM the tail entity.\n\n1. Use the Graph Query tool: What does {{ $json.triple.tail }} point to?\n2. Is this the right type of entity to receive this relation?\n3. Round 2+ considerations: {{ JSON.stringify($json.agentResponses) }}\n\nRespond JSON: { \"verdict\": \"CORRECT/INCORRECT\", \"confidence\": 0-10, \"evidence\": [], \"reasoning\": \"...\" }"
            },
            "id": "agent-tail-forward",
            "name": "3c. Tail Forward Agent",
            "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
            "typeVersion": 1.7,
            "position": [
                690,
                550
            ]
        },
        {
            "parameters": {
                "promptType": "define",
                "text": "=## TAIL BACKWARD AGENT - Round {{ $json.discussionRound }}\n\n**Triple:** ({{ $json.triple.head }}) --[{{ $json.triple.relation }}]--> ({{ $json.triple.tail }})\n**Source:** {{ $json.sourceText || 'No source provided' }}\n\nYou analyze INCOMING relations TO the tail entity.\n\n1. Use the Graph Query tool: What else points TO {{ $json.triple.tail }}?\n2. Do other entities use similar relations to point here?\n3. Round 2+ considerations: {{ JSON.stringify($json.agentResponses) }}\n\nRespond JSON: { \"verdict\": \"CORRECT/INCORRECT\", \"confidence\": 0-10, \"evidence\": [], \"reasoning\": \"...\" }"
            },
            "id": "agent-tail-backward",
            "name": "3d. Tail Backward Agent",
            "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
            "typeVersion": 1.7,
